Name: Fran
Instructions: Complete 21-15-9 reps of Thrusters and Pull-ups.
Scaling Options: Reduce reps, lighten load, or modify gymnastics (e.g., banded pull-ups, lighter KB, shortened run distances).
Target Stimulus: High-intensity sprint with pulling and barbell cycling.
Coach Notes: Go unbroken if possible; keep transitions tight; control breathing.
Description: One of CrossFit's original benchmark Girl workouts created by Greg Glassman to test metabolic conditioning via thrusters and pull-ups.
Warmup: 5-10 min general cardio (row/jog/bike); Air squats and goblet squats progression, ankle mobility; Scapular pull-ups, ring rows or banded pull-ups
Coaching-Cues: Pace the workout according to the time domain; avoid all-out opening bursts unless short sprint. Break thrusters into manageable sets; keep front rack tight. Use kip efficiently; consider banded pull-ups to keep turnover high.
